    </header>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        AI News Blog uses a sophisticated <strong>Multi-Agent System (MAS)</strong> powered by large language models 
        to automatically curate high-quality AI news. Three specialized AI agents work together to ensure only the 
        most relevant and valuable content reaches your inbox.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Workflow Diagram -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">5-Stage Filtering Pipeline</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Stage 1: Data Collection -->
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">
            1
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üì° Multi-Source Aggregation</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">Fetch articles from:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-1">
              <li><strong>arXiv</strong>: Latest research papers (CS.AI, CS.LG, CS.CL)</li>
              <li><strong>RSS Feeds</strong>: TechCrunch, VentureBeat, MIT Tech Review, Google Research</li>
              <li><strong>Hacker News</strong>: Top AI-related discussions</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-2">Fetches ~120-150 articles per day</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 2: Categorization -->
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-purple-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">
            2
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üè∑Ô∏è Smart Categorization</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">Hybrid system (rule-based + LLM) assigns articles to categories:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-1">
              <li><strong>ML Monday</strong>: Machine learning research & applications</li>
              <li><strong>Tech Tuesday</strong>: Industry news & product launches</li>
              <li><strong>Web Wednesday</strong>: Web development & frameworks</li>
              <li><strong>Thought Thursday</strong>: AI ethics & societal impact</li>
              <li><strong>Fun Friday</strong>: Creative AI applications & humor</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 3: Agent 1 - Relevance Gate -->
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-green-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">
            3
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üö™ Agent 1: Relevance Gatekeeper</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
              <strong>Binary filter</strong> - Strict YES/NO relevance check using category-specific examples.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg mt-2">
              <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">Example prompt for ML Monday:</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm italic">
                "Is this article relevant to machine learning researchers/developers? 
                YES if: new models, training techniques, benchmarks, applications. 
                NO if: general tech news, unrelated AI hype, business only."
              </p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-2">Fail mode: <strong>Closed</strong> (reject on error)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Typical rejection rate: ~80%</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 4: Agent 2 - Quality Scorer -->
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-yellow-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">
            4
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">‚≠ê Agent 2: Quality Scorer</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
              <strong>Multi-dimensional assessment</strong> - Rates articles on 3 criteria (0-10 each):
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-1">
              <li><strong>Novelty</strong>: New methods, breakthrough results, fresh perspectives</li>
              <li><strong>Practical Applicability</strong>: Can developers/researchers use this?</li>
              <li><strong>Significance</strong>: Impact on field, industry relevance</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
              Weighted average calculated. Articles below <strong>6.0/10</strong> are rejected.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-2">Fail mode: <strong>Neutral</strong> (assign 5.0 on error)</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Stage 5: Agent 3 - Negative Filter -->
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-red-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">
            5
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">üö´ Agent 3: Negative Filter (Veto Power)</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
              <strong>Final safety net</strong> - Rejects articles that waste readers' time:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-1">
              <li>Vague announcements without substance</li>
              <li>Pure marketing hype</li>
              <li>Redundant content (already covered)</li>
              <li>Clickbait or misleading titles</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
              Rates "waste-of-time" factor 0-10. Articles above <strong>5.0</strong> are vetoed.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-2">Fail mode: <strong>Open</strong> (don't reject on error)</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Performance Stats -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-purple-50 rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
